<pageContent>
    <id><![CDATA[OTS_SA_R4_D030]]></id>
	<title><![CDATA[<Introtext style="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold; color:#cc0033; margin:10px -5px 10px 5px; width:738px; padding:5px 0 5px 5px; background:#e8e8e8; border-bottom:1px solid #333; display:block;">New Opportunity</Introtext>]]></title>
	<title2><![CDATA[]]></title2>
	<instructions><![CDATA[<welcomeText style=" font-family:Helvetica; font-size:11pt; line-height:18pt; text-align:justify; font-weight:bold; color:#333; display:block; margin:0 10px 10px">How do you respond to Dr. Gomez’s request?</welcomeText >]]></instructions>
	<choices>
		<choice>
			<id><![CDATA[1]]></id>
			<isCorrect><![CDATA[NO]]></isCorrect>
			<choiceText><![CDATA[<welcomeText style=" font-family:Helvetica; font-size:12pt; line-height:18pt; text-align:justify; font-weight:normal; color:#333; display:block; margin:0 10px 10px"><b>A</b>. Quickly get a payor map, Discharge Checklist, and ACCESS brochure  in front of Dr. Cardonza. You have developed a level of trust with both Dr. Cardonza and Dr. Gomez, and you have a good understanding of their priorities. You can move forward. </welcomeText>]]></choiceText>
			<KPIs totalScore="5">
				<KPI marks="0"><![CDATA[Customer Results Score]]></KPI>
				<KPI marks="5"><![CDATA[Sales Progress Score]]></KPI>
				<KPI marks="0"><![CDATA[Trusted Advisor Relationship Score]]></KPI>
			</KPIs>
			<branchTo><![CDATA[OTS_SA_R4_D030_A010]]></branchTo>
		</choice>
		<choice>
			<id><![CDATA[2]]></id>
			<isCorrect><![CDATA[YES]]></isCorrect>
			<choiceText><![CDATA[<welcomeText style=" font-family:Helvetica; font-size:12pt; line-height:18pt; text-align:justify; font-weight:normal; color:#333; display:block; margin:0 10px 10px"><b>B</b>. This is a new opportunity. Prior to providing more information, make sure to explore and identify any other needs and to confirm how this fits with the department priorities and desired patient goals you have already identified with Dr. Cardonza and Dr. Gomez.</welcomeText>]]></choiceText>
			<KPIs totalScore="30">
				<KPI marks="10"><![CDATA[Customer Results Score]]></KPI>
				<KPI marks="10"><![CDATA[Sales Progress Score]]></KPI>
				<KPI marks="10"><![CDATA[Trusted Advisor Relationship Score]]></KPI>
			</KPIs>
			<branchTo><![CDATA[OTS_SA_R4_D030_B010]]></branchTo>
		</choice>
		<choice>
			<id><![CDATA[3]]></id>
			<isCorrect><![CDATA[NO]]></isCorrect>
			<choiceText><![CDATA[<welcomeText style=" font-family:Helvetica; font-size:12pt; line-height:18pt; text-align:justify; font-weight:normal; color:#333; display:block; margin:0 10px 10px"><b>C</b>. Find out what other types of patients with hyponatremia in heart failure that Dr. Cardonza might be interested in now that he and Dr. Gomez are more open to your product. Make sure that you get the cardiology department prescribing your product for as many patient types as possible. </welcomeText>]]></choiceText>
			<KPIs totalScore="5">
				<KPI marks="0"><![CDATA[Customer Results Score]]></KPI>
				<KPI marks="5"><![CDATA[Sales Progress Score]]></KPI>
				<KPI marks="0"><![CDATA[Trusted Advisor Relationship Score]]></KPI>
			</KPIs>
			<branchTo><![CDATA[OTS_SA_R4_D030_A010]]></branchTo>
		</choice>
		<choice>
			<id><![CDATA[4]]></id>
			<isCorrect><![CDATA[NO]]></isCorrect>
			<choiceText><![CDATA[<welcomeText style=" font-family:Helvetica; font-size:12pt; line-height:18pt; text-align:justify; font-weight:normal; color:#333; display:block; margin:0 10px 10px"><b>D</b>. Now that Dr. Cardonza and Dr. Gomez appear to be in the “evaluating the trial” phase of the cycle, you need to get information to them on insurance coverage and patient cost so you can ensure they have their questions answered up front and lessen the likelihood that they will explore other alternatives. </welcomeText>]]></choiceText>
			<KPIs totalScore="-10">
				<KPI marks="0"><![CDATA[Customer Results Score]]></KPI>
				<KPI marks="-5"><![CDATA[Sales Progress Score]]></KPI>
				<KPI marks="-5"><![CDATA[Trusted Advisor Relationship Score]]></KPI>
			</KPIs>
			<branchTo><![CDATA[OTS_SA_R4_D030_A010]]></branchTo>
		</choice>
		<!--<feedbackText><![CDATA[]]></feedbackText>-->
	</choices>
	 <summary><![CDATA[<welcomeText style=" font-family:Helvetica; font-size:12pt; line-height:18pt; text-align:justify; font-weight:normal; color:#333; display:block; margin:0 10px 10px">This is a new prescribing cycle, and it needs to be treated accordingly. Choice A assumes that the understanding you have of the cardiology department’s priorities fits with this new opportunity as well, an assumption that could cause problems later in the cycle. Choices C and D both move you forward too quickly without ensuring that you have met all the customer’s needs in this phase, possibly creating mistrust later in the prescribing cycle. It is best to treat this as a new prescribing cycle and quickly identify any additional needs the customer may have so you can move forward with this new opportunity confidently. Choice B is the best choice.</welcomeText>]]></summary>
</pageContent>